article.description: Jonathan Williams scored 24 points with three 3-pointers and Toledo dominated Western Michigan in an 89-62 win on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 24, Toledo beats Western Michigan 89-62
article.linkText: Williams scores 24, Toledo beats Western Michigan 89-62
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Jonathan Williams scored 24 points with three 3-pointers and Toledo dominated Western Michigan in an 89-62 win on Tuesday night. Nathan Boothe scored 16 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, Jordan Lauf had 12, Nate Navigato added 12 -- all on 3-pointers -- and Zach Garber had a career-high 11 boards. Stuckey Mosley made a career-high nine assists for the Rockets (13-9, 4-5), who entered the game tied for fourth place in the Mid-American conference's West Division. Leading 44-30 at halftime behind Williams' 15 points, the Rockets pulled further ahead on an 11-0 run and led by 35 points with 3:46 left on Taylor Adway's layup. The Rockets outrebounded the Broncos 42-20, outscored them 34-18 in the paint and made 10 of 24 3-pointers. Thomas Wilder scored 20 points and Josh Davis added 12 for Western Michigan (9-13, 3-6), which has yet to win on the road this season.
